        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/william_kelley/{size}/2314_2.png",
        "created_at": "2021-07-09T23:34:28.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"171942\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>I just received an offer for some '18\u2019s and Lafon\u2019s Meursault Genevrieres was priced higher than Roulot\u2019s. This surprised me. I feel like it\u2019s almost always the opposite. Is Roulot\u2019s not Domaine\u2013he does not distinguish any more I know\u2013or is it a sign of a broader change?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Roulot\u2019s Genevrieres is a n\u00e9goce wine under the Jean-Marc Roulot label, it\u2019s quite clearly distinguished.</p>",
