      {
        "id": 3194809,
        "name": "Michael Bowden",
        "username": "Michael_Bowden",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/e5b9ba/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2021-07-10T01:47:11.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group quote-modified\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"171942\">\n<blockquote>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"171942\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>I just received an offer for some '18\u2019s and Lafon\u2019s Meursault Genevrieres was priced higher than Roulot\u2019s. This surprised me. I feel like it\u2019s almost always the opposite. Is Roulot\u2019s not Domaine\u2013he does not distinguish any more I know\u2013or is it a sign of a broader change?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Roulot\u2019s Genevrieres is a n\u00e9goce wine under the Jean-Marc Roulot label, it\u2019s quite clearly distinguished.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>On the label yes, but in an email (assumption) offer the person might have just said \u201cRoulot\u201d which isn\u2019t exactly honest but not exactly dishonest either - tricky wordplay.</p>",
